verbose_text: Similarly, the OCM promoted cell invasion in ES-2 cells could be inhibited by anti-CXCR2 and anti-GRO-alpha antibodies, but not by anti-IL-8, suggesting that both IL-8 and GRO-alpha function separately in OCM to promote the tumorigenicity of ovarian cancer.
evidence: invasion in ES-2 cells could be inhibited by anti-CXCR2 and anti-GRO-alpha antibodies, but not by anti-IL-8
